        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "What is the use case where a plugin needs to exit nvim in the middle of a fast callback? It is not really clear from the linked issue.\r\n\r\nMy gut feeling is that this should be exceptionally rare (almost like an `abort()` panic in the first place), and then we could just skip the `event_teardown()` step instead. in the case a plugin just discovers an exit _condition_ but is fine with a clean exit sometime a bit later, `vim.schedule` exists. ",
            "created_at": "2026-05-20T10:51:05Z",
