        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Many thanks for your efforts!\r\n\r\nI forgot mention this only happened in our ci and I've found a workaround later by replacing `os.exit()` to `vim.cmd.cquit()`. (wrap `vim.schedule(os.exit)` again can also work)\r\n\r\nI'm not sure what's the root cause, since from the code it already \"schedule\" the exit:\r\nhttps://github.com/ibhagwan/fzf-lua/blob/311a630292310ea3bfe46dd616e17f283e975801/lua/fzf-lua/libuv.lua#L547-L559 \r\n\r\nAnyway it's no longer an issue for us. Feel free to close https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39783 if not worth to maintain complexity here.",
